menuconfig TENSOR_SUBSYSTEM
	bool "Tensor object subsystem"
	help
	  Enable first-class, file-descriptor-backed tensor objects for sharing
	  validated multidimensional memory between userspace, kernel subsystems,
	  and DMA-capable devices. This provides common tensor object lifecycle,
	  synchronization, mapping, accounting, and tracing infrastructure.

if TENSOR_SUBSYSTEM

config TENSOR_NATIVE
	tristate "Native tensor objects"
	depends on MMU
	select DMA_SHARED_BUFFER
	help
	  Create validated, mmap-able tensor objects through /dev/tensor_native.
	  Each tensor is represented by an anonymous file descriptor and exposes
	  sequence-based signal, wait, poll, DMA-BUF, and kernel mapping APIs.

	  If built as a module, the module will be called tensor_native.

endif
